WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:11.480 --> 00:00:16.242
Hail Jesus and Mary, dear subscribers of the YouTube channel of the Association "Croatia for Life".

00:00:16.242 --> 00:00:22.407
We are here on Trešnjevka, in the parish of St. Josip, in their premises.

00:00:22.407 --> 00:00:27.619
Because this weekend we have a conference for life "Now choose Life",

00:00:27.619 --> 00:00:30.963
the 6th in a row organized by our Association.

00:00:30.963 --> 00:00:36.215
One of the speakers will be Ruth Rawlins, from the United Kingdom.

00:00:36.215 --> 00:00:40.218
Today we will talk to her, we will conduct the conversation in English, 

00:00:40.218 --> 00:00:45.158
so you will have subtitles below for those who may not understand well.

00:00:45.158 --> 00:00:46.040
Let's begin.

00:00:46.040 --> 00:00:47.598
Hi Ruth.

00:00:47.598 --> 00:00:48.613
Hi Lydia.

00:00:48.613 --> 00:00:53.721
I'm so happy to have you here. Thank you for coming to our conference and here in our podcast.

00:00:53.721 --> 00:00:55.531
It's wonderful to be here.

00:00:55.531 --> 00:01:01.845
I will love that you introduce yourself so people know with whom we are talking.

00:01:01.845 --> 00:01:05.231
Okay, so I'm Ruth Rawlins and I've come all the way from London England

00:01:05.231 --> 00:01:12.524
and I work in Communications for the Center for bioethical reform UK.

00:01:12.524 --> 00:01:14.853
CBR UK for short.

00:01:14.853 --> 00:01:21.931
And we're basically working to educate on the humanity of the baby in the womb

00:01:21.931 --> 00:01:27.223
and expose the reality of abortion and support women who have been through abortion.

00:01:27.223 --> 00:01:36.669
So our podcasts are something like testimony and spiritual talk and also official talk.

00:01:36.669 --> 00:01:43.542
Can you please tell us something about your background, childhood, religion and everything

00:01:43.542 --> 00:01:46.912
and how did you get involved in the pro-life movement?

00:01:46.912 --> 00:01:47.648
Okay.

00:01:47.648 --> 00:01:55.695
So, I grew up in a Christian home and I never really heard anything about abortion at church,

00:01:55.695 --> 00:01:57.815
it wasn't spoken about.

00:01:57.815 --> 00:02:06.935
I remember in school in religious studies we did talk about abortion and writing an essay about it.

00:02:06.935 --> 00:02:11.592
And actually funnily enough I found that essay recently

00:02:11.592 --> 00:02:17.864
and I noticed that I had written a rape exception, which is interesting.

00:02:17.864 --> 00:02:20.000
My views have clearly changed now.

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:25.213
But my parents had put across to me that abortion was wrong

00:02:25.213 --> 00:02:27.578
so I knew that it wasn't a good thing.

00:02:27.578 --> 00:02:29.765
I knew that it was killing a baby.

00:02:29.765 --> 00:02:32.848
And fast forward to when I went to University.

00:02:32.848 --> 00:02:35.850
I actually walked away from the Lord.

00:02:35.850 --> 00:02:39.775
I think I thought the grass was greener on the other side,

00:02:39.775 --> 00:02:42.984
if that saying makes sense in Croatian.

00:02:42.984 --> 00:02:49.236
And I just got into a bad relationship, ungodly relationship.

00:02:49.236 --> 00:02:52.378
I ended up becoming pregnant in my final year of University

00:02:52.378 --> 00:02:59.002
and because I knew that abortion was wrong, it didn't enter my head.

00:02:59.002 --> 00:03:04.662
And I'm so grateful to God and to my parents for that because otherwise,

00:03:04.662 --> 00:03:07.382
you know, my child might not be here today.

00:03:07.382 --> 00:03:12.873
That was my path of coming back to God.

00:03:12.873 --> 00:03:20.906
When I had my baby dedicated at church and then I got baptized the next month.

00:03:20.906 --> 00:03:28.289
So obviously having a daughter and being a single mother

00:03:28.289 --> 00:03:30.667
had some challenges that came with that.

00:03:30.667 --> 00:03:38.016
But it was an exciting time for me because I was discovering more and more about God

00:03:38.016 --> 00:03:42.399
and fellowship him with lots of other parents and children,

00:03:42.399 --> 00:03:44.292
mothers and children at that time.

00:03:44.292 --> 00:03:48.845
So I enjoyed those years of raising my daughter up.

00:03:48.845 --> 00:03:57.466
The issue of abortion came back into my life when I was working for my church for a year.

00:03:57.466 --> 00:04:00.549
I was doing a voluntary year at my church.

00:04:00.549 --> 00:04:06.625
I came in because at my church they used to rent out rooms to the local Council.

00:04:06.625 --> 00:04:12.192
And there was a sign on the door and it said „pregnancy decision making meeting“

00:04:12.192 --> 00:04:15.345
in room three.

00:04:15.345 --> 00:04:20.939
And my heart was grieved, what decisions are there to be made in pregnancy

00:04:20.939 --> 00:04:24.331
and why is this being held in a church.

00:04:24.331 --> 00:04:31.942
When I spoke to the people at the church who worked in administration they said:

00:04:31.942 --> 00:04:34.516
„You don't know what it is they're talking about.“

00:04:34.516 --> 00:04:40.270
But I knew it was abortion and at that moment I had to find a quiet room

00:04:40.270 --> 00:04:46.633
and I just wept and I think the Lord really wept through me.

00:04:46.633 --> 00:04:51.077
And I felt my heart break for the issue,

00:04:51.077 --> 00:04:56.358
for the babies that are being killed and I felt the heart of God actually in that moment.

00:04:56.358 --> 00:05:02.833
I started reading about the life of William Wilberforce and was really inspired

00:05:02.833 --> 00:05:06.961
because he wrote down his two life goals.

00:05:06.961 --> 00:05:10.000
One was to see an end to the transatlantic slave trade.

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:14.849
Now, William Wilberforce was a politician in the UK

00:05:14.849 --> 00:05:19.037
and he's been credited actually in history for being

00:05:19.037 --> 00:05:22.121
fundamental in ending the transatlantic slave.

00:05:22.121 --> 00:05:27.364
So he wrote that down as one of his goals and so I decided to write down my goals

00:05:27.364 --> 00:05:29.443
and ending an abortion was one of them.

00:05:29.443 --> 00:05:34.136
But that stayed in my journal for a couple of years.

00:05:34.136 --> 00:05:38.131
I didn't really do anything until I saw a program,

00:05:38.131 --> 00:05:43.574
a conference called the Wilberforce Academy and they were talking about abortion.

00:05:43.574 --> 00:05:45.033
So I knew I had to be there.

00:05:45.033 --> 00:05:46.864
And I went along and at that conference

00:05:46.864 --> 00:05:50.647
I met my now boss from CBR UK.

00:05:50.647 --> 00:05:54.561
They showed us a video of an abortion procedure.

00:09:24.800 --> 00:09:32.541
And seeing that image, seeing the video of a baby's body being ripped apart,

00:09:32.541 --> 00:09:38.033
limb by limb, I knew at that moment that to do nothing was no longer an option.

00:09:38.033 --> 00:09:42.828
So after about a year of volunteering I got involved and

00:09:42.828 --> 00:09:46.146
I've been working full-time ever since, 10 years.

00:09:46.146 --> 00:09:49.112
I'll tell you a little bit more about what they do shortly.

00:09:49.112 --> 00:09:49.888
That's so good.

00:09:49.888 --> 00:09:53.449
Can you tell me something about your pregnancy.

00:09:53.449 --> 00:10:00.089
While you were pregnant, was there people or members of your family

00:10:00.089 --> 00:10:03.686
or someone who didn't want you to be pregnant anymore?

00:10:03.686 --> 00:10:10.000
Who suggested you to do an abortion because of your school, or your college,

00:10:10.000 --> 00:10:13.750
or your career, future, or something like that? How was that?

00:10:13.750 --> 00:10:15.771
I mean the timing was good.

00:10:15.771 --> 00:10:19.375
I guess that I was just coming to the end of my three years.

00:10:19.375 --> 00:10:25.169
Although I found out when I was taking my final exams, I think I failed that exam.

00:10:25.169 --> 00:10:29.047
But I had more or less finished my course.

00:10:29.047 --> 00:10:36.445
Again I was very blessed that my parents were very supportive because they were Christian.

00:10:36.445 --> 00:10:43.408
And as much as it was difficult to tell them, I knew that they wouldn't disown me,

00:10:43.408 --> 00:10:45.811
that they would support me.

00:10:45.811 --> 00:10:50.671
When I rang them up, I mean they didn't know that I was in a relationship,

00:10:50.671 --> 00:10:56.426
so they were disappointed you know, cuz I wasn't in the same city as them.

00:10:56.426 --> 00:11:00.594
But when I told them, they were very supportive.

00:11:00.594 --> 00:11:05.361
Most of my family were supportive.

00:11:05.361 --> 00:11:09.907
I think there was someone who maybe suggested that I have an abortion,

00:11:09.907 --> 00:11:13.306
but obviously my parents wouldn't have any of that.

00:11:13.306 --> 00:11:18.795
It didn't, as I said, it didn't enter my head because as much as I'd walked away from God

00:11:18.795 --> 00:11:22.389
there was still a fear of God deep in my hear.

00:11:22.389 --> 00:11:25.346
I knew that, that was something I couldn't do.

00:11:25.346 --> 00:11:29.435
And I don't say that to say that I'm great.

00:11:29.435 --> 00:11:35.005
I say that because my heart breaks for all the women that haven't been raised with that.

00:11:35.005 --> 00:11:41.634
That have been raised and their parents have said, you know don't bring any illegitimate children

00:11:41.634 --> 00:11:44.780
into this family and things like that.

00:11:44.780 --> 00:11:46.360
Because of the shame…

00:11:46.360 --> 00:11:49.445
Exactly, things like that can seal their abortions.

00:11:49.445 --> 00:11:53.641
I know women like this, you know, they're my friends.

00:11:53.641 --> 00:11:57.859
I can only thank God that by his grace I had support around me

00:11:57.859 --> 00:12:03.421
and that I had the knowledge of the truth,

00:12:03.421 --> 00:12:10.711
that no matter how challenging a situation is, to kill my child will never solve anything.

00:12:10.711 --> 00:12:13.410
God has been great, he's been faithful.

00:12:13.410 --> 00:12:20.433
My daughter is now 19 and as I got pregnant at Uni, I've just sent her to University.

00:12:20.433 --> 00:12:24.040
So I've come full circle. God has been so great.

00:12:24.040 --> 00:12:29.285
Do you raise her as a prolifer, to be a prolifer?

00:12:29.285 --> 00:12:35.386
Talk to her about the sanctity of life and everything because of your own…?

00:12:35.386 --> 00:12:39.758
Yeah, she was probably around nine when I got into this work,

00:12:39.758 --> 00:12:46.382
so she had seen the images and it's just being raised up with that.

00:12:46.382 --> 00:12:54.640
It's just obvious to her that this is an evil.

00:12:54.640 --> 00:13:00.387
Can you please tell us something about the CBR UK, what do you do?

00:13:00.387 --> 00:13:06.788
I know about the pictures and everything and we met each other and at 2014,

00:13:06.788 --> 00:13:10.932
it was 10 years ago now in London.

00:13:10.932 --> 00:13:15.623
I was really thrilled talking to you about your work,

00:13:15.623 --> 00:13:20.906
so can you please explain to us how is it going on there?

00:13:20.906 --> 00:13:22.761
Our main thing is education.

00:13:22.761 --> 00:13:28.648
We believe that the reason so many people in society, in the UK anyway,

00:13:28.648 --> 00:13:37.032
are what's called pro-choice, we're talking about that they are pro choice to kill a baby.

00:13:37.032 --> 00:13:41.738
But they haven't really understood exactly what that choice is.

00:13:41.738 --> 00:13:46.904
And so that's why we believe it's our job and the job of every social reformer

00:13:46.904 --> 00:13:52.136
to show the humanity of the victims of abortion, the babies in the womb

00:13:52.136 --> 00:13:55.135
and obviously we know the women are the secondary victims.

00:13:55.135 --> 00:13:58.134
And to show the reality of abortion.

00:13:58.134 --> 00:14:04.025
We use images which is the easiest way to convey that.

00:14:04.025 --> 00:14:06.505
Sure we can use words and words are powerful.

00:14:06.505 --> 00:14:11.622
But when people see an image of, you know, a baby, a living baby in the womb.

00:14:11.622 --> 00:14:16.210
They can't argue with the fact that's a little human being.

00:14:16.210 --> 00:14:23.535
Some people may try, because you know they don't want to change their viewpoint on abortion.

00:14:23.535 --> 00:14:27.976
But when people see it, they see the eyes, they see the fingers,

00:14:27.976 --> 00:14:33.459
they see the toes, as young as seven weeks.

00:14:33.459 --> 00:14:38.849
Many people are surprised because they're used to hearing these words like

00:14:38.849 --> 00:14:42.813
'oh it's a clump of cells', 'it's pregnancy tissue'.

00:14:42.813 --> 00:14:46.128
But when we hold up an image of a living baby in the womb,

00:14:46.128 --> 00:14:49.136
even small children will walk past and say 'baby'.

00:14:49.136 --> 00:14:51.602
They recognize what it is,

00:14:51.602 --> 00:14:56.184
that it's a human being and the images of what happens

00:14:56.184 --> 00:15:01.598
to that baby during an abortion expose the injustice.

00:15:01.598 --> 00:15:07.083
And so we take these images on big banners like, about two foot by two foot.

00:15:07.083 --> 00:15:10.513
We take them into the city center, we hold these banners up.

00:15:10.513 --> 00:15:13.417
At the top of the living baby, we have the word 'life'.

00:15:13.417 --> 00:15:17.723
At the top of the aborted baby we have the word 'choice question mark',

00:15:17.723 --> 00:15:20.128
to show the reality of that choice.

00:15:20.128 --> 00:15:23.147
We just simply engage the public walking by.

00:15:23.147 --> 00:15:26.891
Many people will stop, have a look, have conversations with us

00:15:26.891 --> 00:15:30.548
and it's important to note that we're not protesting abortion,

00:15:30.548 --> 00:15:34.804
because none of our literature says 'stop abortion', 'abortion is wrong'.

00:15:34.804 --> 00:15:39.128
We're not chanting, we're not shouting or anything.

00:15:39.128 --> 00:15:44.732
But when we hold up an image of an aborted baby, abortion protests itself.

00:15:44.732 --> 00:15:48.787
We take leaflets and we hand them to the public

00:15:48.787 --> 00:15:51.160
and we simply ask what do you think about abortion.

00:15:51.160 --> 00:15:58.265
And we allow that conversation to take them to the place where they have to start thinking

00:15:58.265 --> 00:16:01.809
about what happens in that abortion procedure.

00:16:01.809 --> 00:16:07.682
Is it a human being and is that a human being being killed and if so,

00:16:07.682 --> 00:16:12.443
is that something we should be doing as a so-called civilized society.

00:16:12.443 --> 00:16:16.975
So, it's very effective, it's very powerful, we see people change their minds.

00:16:16.975 --> 00:16:21.813
Obviously, some people walk on by, it's busy city.

00:16:21.813 --> 00:16:28.069
Other people do get angry and abuse us because maybe they've been through abortion

00:16:28.069 --> 00:16:32.193
or maybe they just don't want to see a change.

00:16:32.193 --> 00:16:36.852
We probably all heard that: 'I want right to choose',

00:16:36.852 --> 00:16:41.149
whether it's a man who wants the right to get rid of any babies

00:16:41.149 --> 00:16:44.144
so that he can have sex without consequences or whether

00:16:44.144 --> 00:16:49.232
it's the woman that has believed that lie that somehow it's empowering to women

00:16:49.232 --> 00:16:51.040
to be able to kill their babies.

00:16:51.040 --> 00:16:53.569
So, we do get some opposition

00:16:53.569 --> 00:16:57.415
but we wouldn't be doing this if we didn't see the fruit,

00:16:57.415 --> 00:16:59.568
if we didn't see the effectiveness

00:16:59.568 --> 00:17:04.483
and we just know that if we can continue to expose what's going on,

00:17:04.483 --> 00:17:09.651
then people will change their mind and you can't end an injustice,

00:17:09.651 --> 00:17:13.600
you can't change the law, until you've changed public opinion.

00:17:13.600 --> 00:17:18.236
Can you please tell us where did you get your pictures for the displays,

00:17:18.236 --> 00:17:24.153
because I know on some of them you compare body of the baby with a coin

00:17:24.153 --> 00:17:26.076
and it's really effective.

00:17:26.076 --> 00:17:27.882
So where did you get them?

00:17:27.882 --> 00:17:34.805
The aborted images were got by the Center for bioethical reform in America

00:17:34.805 --> 00:17:39.806
and they sent a photography into where abortions were taking place.

00:17:39.806 --> 00:17:45.678
They sent the coins, so the actual baby's body part were taken on the coins,

00:17:45.678 --> 00:17:49.005
just as a size reference.

00:17:49.005 --> 00:17:52.817
They've been signed by an abortionist to say that this is the actual age,

00:17:52.817 --> 00:17:55.399
that they're representing.

00:17:55.399 --> 00:18:00.699
With the living images we get them from an organization called Education resource fund

00:18:00.699 --> 00:18:08.754
and they're a scientific organization that provide resources, so we use their images.

00:18:08.754 --> 00:18:15.442
Just to say, with the living images there is the same technology used that Nasa uses

00:18:15.442 --> 00:18:21.800
to take images of the moon, because obviously you can't get really close so they piece all.

00:18:21.800 --> 00:18:26.134
They take photographs inside the womb and they piece all the images together

00:18:26.134 --> 00:18:30.177
to create that whole baby, so it's not an animated picture in any way.

00:18:30.177 --> 00:18:32.745
It's a real photograph.

00:18:32.745 --> 00:18:39.786
And I think it really has so much effection on a people who passes by.

00:18:39.786 --> 00:18:45.189
They are just living their lives and suddenly they have to see

00:18:45.189 --> 00:18:48.946
the aborted baby and parts of their body.

00:18:48.946 --> 00:18:54.823
Can you please tell us something from the street, some kind of testimony,

00:18:54.823 --> 00:19:01.123
maybe first some good and then some bad, one attack or something like that?

00:19:01.123 --> 00:19:04.145
And how you take care of your volunteers?

00:19:04.145 --> 00:19:10.068
I know you put cameras and you work also with the police.

00:19:10.068 --> 00:19:14.523
So a little bit about the working on the street.

00:19:14.523 --> 00:19:19.268
In the UK we've got 12 teams around the country in different cities

00:19:19.268 --> 00:19:21.714
and each team has a team leader.

00:19:21.714 --> 00:19:27.197
And when we asked our teams and our volunteers why is that they chose to work with us,

00:19:27.197 --> 00:19:30.023
they said that it's the training they receive,

00:19:30.023 --> 00:19:34.150
and they felt they were really looked after.

00:19:34.150 --> 00:19:37.625
So it's very important to us that we do everything properly because,

00:19:37.625 --> 00:19:41.913
as you know, just being pro-lifers particularly in the UK,

00:19:41.913 --> 00:19:45.613
we're already accused of so many false accusations.

00:19:45.613 --> 00:19:52.932
Like that we scream murderer or we throw holy water on people outside clinics.

00:19:52.932 --> 00:19:58.333
But we simply don't do that and I don't know any pro-lifers in the UK that do that.

00:19:58.333 --> 00:20:02.866
But those are lies, so it's very important that we have security cameras

00:20:02.866 --> 00:20:07.661
on our displays, we always tell the police when we're going to be doing a display

00:20:07.661 --> 00:20:09.426
so they know that we're here.

00:20:09.426 --> 00:20:14.117
They'll sometimes come and defend our right to free speech.

00:20:14.117 --> 00:20:18.765
Because a lot of times passes by think we have no right to display these images.

00:20:18.765 --> 00:20:24.657
Our images have been passed in a court of law to say that we can show them on the street.

00:20:24.657 --> 00:20:27.892
So we don't get so much opposition from the police anymore,

00:20:27.892 --> 00:20:29.808
since we got that from court.

00:20:29.808 --> 00:20:33.770
We do look after our volunteers and training,

00:20:33.770 --> 00:20:39.323
as well we train them in pro-life apologetics and that just means that they know how to engage,

00:20:39.323 --> 00:20:46.113
how to love the person and speak in a loving tone to the people they meet on the streets.

00:20:46.113 --> 00:20:49.735
It's very important for us that is all in place.

00:20:49.735 --> 00:20:54.397
And when we're on the streets obviously the most encouraging thing

00:20:54.397 --> 00:20:56.676
is always going to be a life saved.

00:20:56.676 --> 00:21:02.029
And the first life that I witnessed when I got into this work, we're going back 10 years.

00:21:02.029 --> 00:21:04.953
We used to go outside the Department of Health,

00:21:04.953 --> 00:21:09.747
which is kind of the government building that make the decisions on health.

00:21:09.747 --> 00:21:12.869
And I felt in my heart I wanted to be outside the clinics,

00:21:12.869 --> 00:21:16.616
that's where the killing was happening, that's the front lines.

00:21:16.616 --> 00:21:21.484
So I took my team outside a place in London called Brixton

00:21:21.484 --> 00:21:24.341
and it's called Mary stopes clinic.

00:21:24.341 --> 00:21:27.409
A couple of my friends had abortions there in the past,

00:21:27.409 --> 00:21:30.891
so it was quite personal to me and to us.

00:21:30.891 --> 00:21:39.300
We met a lady that was coming in for her second appointment with the medical pills.

00:21:39.300 --> 00:21:44.326
She'd taken the first pill the day before and your viewers may know

00:21:44.326 --> 00:21:49.513
that that pill thins the lining of the womb and the baby can come away from the womb

00:21:49.513 --> 00:21:52.845
and then it will die because it can't get any further nutrients.

00:21:52.845 --> 00:21:56.337
When she comes back for the second pill, the pill will expulse the baby.

00:21:56.337 --> 00:22:01.318
So she'd had the first pill, but was coming back for the second pill when she met our volunteers,

00:22:01.318 --> 00:22:06.152
saw the images, she changed her mind and she said „I don't want to go through with this“.

00:22:06.152 --> 00:22:09.483
We took her to another organization called The Good Council Network

00:22:09.483 --> 00:22:14.317
and they scanned the baby and the baby was alive and doing well.

00:22:14.317 --> 00:22:18.955
A lot of prayer went up for that baby and that baby was born.

00:22:18.955 --> 00:22:22.594
I got to visit the mom and hold that beautiful little baby.

00:22:22.594 --> 00:22:25.800
And you know that was 10 years ago, so he's now 10.

00:22:25.800 --> 00:22:32.540
It's just so encouraging to see her sharing images of him on social media,

00:22:32.540 --> 00:22:37.830
his mothers story and just to know that we had not been there that day,

00:22:37.830 --> 00:22:41.706
had his mom not seen those images, he wouldn't be here today.

00:22:41.706 --> 00:22:44.261
So the images are very powerful.

00:22:44.261 --> 00:22:48.657
That was very encouraging.

00:22:48.657 --> 00:22:50.179
We see other stories like that.

00:22:50.179 --> 00:22:53.977
We've moved away, we were not typically outside the clinics

00:22:53.977 --> 00:22:58.731
cuz sometimes these clinics are in side streets, there's not a lot of people walking by.

00:22:58.731 --> 00:23:02.210
So we go to the city center, as well a lot of our teams now.

00:23:02.210 --> 00:23:07.805
But I think the Lord also wanted to show me that it's not just the clinics

00:23:07.805 --> 00:23:09.536
where you're going to see life saved.

00:23:09.536 --> 00:23:12.734
And another day when we were back outside the Department of Health,

00:23:12.734 --> 00:23:21.092
a lady came up to me and she said: „Oh I met you six months ago and I saw the images

00:23:21.092 --> 00:23:25.683
and then a few months later I got pregnant and I thought about abortion

00:23:25.683 --> 00:23:29.015
but then I couldn't get that image out of my mind,

00:23:29.015 --> 00:23:33.325
so I decided I can't go through with an abortion.

00:23:33.325 --> 00:23:35.335
I'm now 3 months pregnant.

00:23:35.335 --> 00:23:36.683
I just want to thank you.“

00:23:36.683 --> 00:23:43.362
It was amazing to have that insight because I think most people wouldn't come back

00:23:43.362 --> 00:23:44.404
to say thank you.

00:23:44.404 --> 00:23:49.296
But I think God wanted me to see that it's not just immediate lives,

00:23:49.296 --> 00:23:50.868
but it's future lives.

00:23:50.868 --> 00:23:54.506
Because every time we hold up those images, there's people going by on the buses,

00:23:54.506 --> 00:23:57.296
there's people walking by, they may not even talk to us.

00:23:57.296 --> 00:24:01.255
But just by seeing it now,

00:24:01.255 --> 00:24:04.459
they've got a reference point and should they find themselves in a situation,

00:24:04.459 --> 00:24:08.658
should a friend of theirs find themselves in that situation, they can speak life,

00:24:08.658 --> 00:24:11.064
they can choose life.

00:24:11.064 --> 00:24:16.651
And that's the power of the truth, that's the power of the images.

00:24:16.651 --> 00:24:20.627
So life saved is always going to be the most encouraging thing.

00:24:20.627 --> 00:24:23.385
We also see a lot of changed minds as well.

00:24:23.385 --> 00:24:25.738
People who will say: „You know I'm pro-choice.“

00:24:25.738 --> 00:24:30.173
And then we sometimes show them the video.

00:24:30.173 --> 00:24:35.859
That's when we've actually gone onto the streets and we take film,

00:24:35.859 --> 00:24:38.298
so if your viewers want to see that they can see.

00:24:38.298 --> 00:24:43.893
And after people see the video of abortion then they go and change their mind.

00:24:43.893 --> 00:24:46.968
It's powerful, it's powerful.

00:24:46.968 --> 00:24:50.572
There's saying that one picture talks more than thousand words.

00:24:50.572 --> 00:24:51.469
Exactly.

00:24:51.469 --> 00:24:53.884
So it's really good to have it in your mind,

00:24:53.884 --> 00:24:59.164
when you pass by and when something happen to your member of family

00:24:59.164 --> 00:25:06.453
or a friend or someone, and you say: „No, no, no, it's not going to look nice, you shouldn't do it.“

00:25:06.453 --> 00:25:07.716
That's so good.

00:25:07.716 --> 00:25:11.860
And what about attacks, what about some opposition?

00:25:11.860 --> 00:25:17.989
The most common thing that people do is they'll try and cover up the images,

00:25:17.989 --> 00:25:22.513
so they'll stand in front of them, they'll bring bed sheets or big flags and

00:25:22.513 --> 00:25:25.441
try and hide the reality of abortion.

00:25:25.441 --> 00:25:30.588
Because it makes them feel uncomfortable and they don't want to change their view.

00:25:30.588 --> 00:25:34.137
It makes it difficult for them to have the view,

00:25:34.137 --> 00:25:37.034
that they support it when they actually see it,

00:25:37.034 --> 00:25:41.189
so that's very common for people to try and cover it up.

00:25:41.189 --> 00:25:46.917
We have been attacked in terms of, normally it's pulling the banners,

00:25:46.917 --> 00:25:50.000
kicking the banners, ripping the banners.

00:25:50.000 --> 00:25:52.214
We've had people spray, paint our banners.

00:25:52.214 --> 00:25:57.216
But we always follow this up and we are grateful to the police

00:25:57.216 --> 00:26:00.748
who have followed up and held them to account.

00:26:00.748 --> 00:26:05.098
We've had the where banners have been destroyed,

00:26:05.098 --> 00:26:08.268
we've got the money from the person who destroyed the banner.

00:26:08.268 --> 00:26:14.140
So we're pleased to hear that but it's just a form of intimidation to try and close us down.

00:26:14.140 --> 00:26:21.073
Obviously people swearing at us, shouting and things like that.

00:26:21.073 --> 00:26:23.872
But it all comes with the work.

00:26:23.872 --> 00:26:29.019
I'm not excusing their behavior, but when you look back at the history of social reform,

00:26:29.019 --> 00:26:37.826
those who want to challenge an injustice that's taking place, they're always hated

00:26:37.826 --> 00:26:42.545
and despised by those who want to keep the status quo.

00:26:42.545 --> 00:26:47.145
By those who benefit somehow from the injustice at hand.

00:26:47.145 --> 00:26:51.747
Whether it was William Wilberforce, whether it was Martin Luther King

00:26:51.747 --> 00:26:55.678
and the civil rights movement in America.

00:26:55.678 --> 00:27:00.780
These people have been loved and hated at the same time.

00:27:00.780 --> 00:27:06.881
I think your viewers who maybe are active pro-lifers can somewhat relate to that.

00:27:06.881 --> 00:27:09.448
It comes with the territory.

00:27:09.448 --> 00:27:19.598
You said earlier when we were talking that pro-choicers hate two things and what are those?

00:27:19.598 --> 00:27:24.273
They hate the truth and they hate prayer.

00:27:24.273 --> 00:27:32.930
Even those so 40 Days for life and CBR.

00:27:32.930 --> 00:27:40.197
We find that they're the two that are really opposed because prayer is obviously spiritual

00:27:40.197 --> 00:27:42.485
and often these people will say they don't even believe in God,

00:27:42.485 --> 00:27:45.017
but yet they still want to shut down prayer.

00:27:45.017 --> 00:27:52.079
We've had someone in the UK arrested for praying privately in her mind.

00:27:52.079 --> 00:27:53.955
Is it Isabelle?

00:27:53.955 --> 00:27:55.359
Isabelle, yes.

00:27:55.359 --> 00:27:59.105
We had her in our conference last year.

00:27:59.105 --> 00:28:02.112
That's what's under attack.

00:28:02.112 --> 00:28:03.907
Praying outside abortion clinics.

00:28:03.907 --> 00:28:06.390
They're trying to put buffer zones as no doubt.

00:28:06.390 --> 00:28:09.398
Isabelle shared and sharing the images.

00:28:09.398 --> 00:28:17.100
So that's Satan who's behind the people who try and shut us down.

00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:23.760
He doesn't want the truth to come out, he's a liar, he's a deceiver and he's a murderer.

00:28:23.760 --> 00:28:25.815
He's been that way since the beginning.

00:28:25.815 --> 00:28:30.397
He hates prayer and he hates the truth.

00:28:30.397 --> 00:28:35.549
That's why it's so important that we do these two things, because they're powerful.

00:28:35.549 --> 00:28:38.235
Because they change public opinion.

00:28:38.235 --> 00:28:40.200
They change the spiritual atmosphere

00:28:40.200 --> 00:28:44.511
and you know we're going to win if we keep doing these things.

00:28:44.511 --> 00:28:50.299
I remember when Isabelle had her testimony

00:28:50.299 --> 00:28:54.406
and she said she was in the buffer zone

00:28:54.406 --> 00:28:58.044
and she was just standing there and they came up to her and said:

00:28:58.044 --> 00:29:01.755
„Are you praying? You know that this is a buffer zone. We know who you are.“

00:29:01.755 --> 00:29:04.322
And she said: „No, I'm just thinking.“

00:29:04.322 --> 00:29:06.280
„What about?“

00:29:06.280 --> 00:29:10.264
And she said: „I don't know, maybe about my sandwich, maybe about the weather.“

00:29:10.264 --> 00:29:13.092
And they said: „No, no, no, we know that you're praying.“

00:29:13.092 --> 00:29:15.891
And they arrested her and it was so crazy.

00:29:15.891 --> 00:29:23.384
She was arrested because of her thoughts. That is so so mad...

00:29:24.798 --> 00:29:28.598
I mean it's crazy.

00:29:28.598 --> 00:29:31.513
I can't say anything more, but it's crazy.

00:29:31.513 --> 00:29:35.130
And they did the same thing, whether it's the same thing

00:29:35.130 --> 00:29:39.801
but at the time of the civil rights in America they wouldn't give

00:29:39.801 --> 00:29:42.377
Martin Luther King and his people permits.

00:29:42.377 --> 00:29:46.771
They said they had to have permits to march and they tried to shut them down.

00:29:46.771 --> 00:29:50.127
Again it's nothing new, it's nothing new.

00:29:50.127 --> 00:29:56.680
The authorities and those that supporting injustice don't want truth and prayer.

00:29:56.680 --> 00:30:02.960
It's always, this is a very tough apostolate

00:30:02.960 --> 00:30:10.472
and very rough and it could be very aggressive and we cry a lot and everything.

00:30:10.472 --> 00:30:13.622
How do you go through it?

00:30:13.622 --> 00:30:18.607
You pray, you read your Bible, you talk to the people who are the same as you

00:30:18.607 --> 00:30:26.094
and what can you say that your life would be if you didn't come into the pro-life?

00:30:26.094 --> 00:30:28.978
So interesting question.

00:30:28.978 --> 00:30:35.179
I've got absolutely no idea what my life would be if I didn't come into this movement

00:30:35.179 --> 00:30:41.694
but all I would know is that having had that call,

00:30:41.694 --> 00:30:46.751
that kind of seeing it and knowing that I have to do something.

00:30:46.751 --> 00:30:50.241
If I ignored that call, my life wouldn't be peaceful,

00:30:50.241 --> 00:30:54.262
I would always know that I was walking away from that

00:30:54.262 --> 00:31:02.859
and I think as much as we talk about the persecution or the opposition that we get,

00:31:02.859 --> 00:31:05.453
there is a joy that comes in it.

00:31:05.453 --> 00:31:09.961
And we read that in the Bible where the disciples came back rejoicing

00:31:09.961 --> 00:31:12.748
because they were persecuted when Jesus sent them out.

00:31:12.748 --> 00:31:17.733
They came back rejoicing that they were persecuted for the sake of the gospel.

00:31:17.733 --> 00:31:20.594
And I think there's that joy that together we're working on this,

00:31:20.594 --> 00:31:24.705
together we're in this fight for justice, we're in this fight for the kingdom of God

00:31:24.705 --> 00:31:32.524
and for the babies and there are rewards when you see fruit from the work

00:31:32.524 --> 00:31:35.709
but it's not rewarding work really.

00:31:35.709 --> 00:31:40.191
I just think we'll get our reward in heaven because only God knows

00:31:40.191 --> 00:31:43.454
how many babies are saved, only God knows.

00:31:43.454 --> 00:31:48.537
That volunteer that is out faithfully praying week after week,

00:31:48.537 --> 00:31:51.932
that volunteer that is out faithfully showing these images

00:31:51.932 --> 00:31:56.218
and sometimes it can feel 'are we having an impact'?

00:31:56.218 --> 00:32:01.253
Like, some days sure, you may have a wonderful conversation or you may see a baby saved.

00:32:01.253 --> 00:32:04.846
But there's other days where you feel like did I have an impact.

00:32:04.846 --> 00:32:08.851
But it's just trusting that you know through the obedience

00:32:08.851 --> 00:32:13.454
and through showing these images, through the prayer, we are having an impact.

00:32:13.454 --> 00:32:20.497
I think that's what keeps us going, remembering the moments where you have seen fruit

00:32:20.497 --> 00:32:26.406
and just being faithful in the little things cuz it's not glamorous work

00:32:26.406 --> 00:32:28.983
by any means but it's important.

00:32:28.983 --> 00:32:37.174
It's just wonderful to have a team of people where everyone play their role.

00:32:37.174 --> 00:32:39.789
There's those that are out faithfully on the street,

00:32:39.789 --> 00:32:42.541
there's those in head office that are organizing,

00:32:42.541 --> 00:32:45.921
there's the leaders that are preparing, there's those who are training,

00:32:45.921 --> 00:32:48.169
there's those who are doing communications

00:32:48.169 --> 00:32:55.867
and all together it's necessary because we're a battle of Truth on the ground.

00:32:55.867 --> 00:32:57.938
But also in the media.

00:32:57.938 --> 00:33:00.536
So what you're doing here in terms of putting us out into the airwaves

00:33:00.536 --> 00:33:03.565
is also so important to win this battle.

00:33:03.565 --> 00:33:07.098
For truth and for the hearts of the people.

00:33:07.098 --> 00:33:10.567
That they will see and wake up to the fact

00:33:10.567 --> 00:33:14.308
that we've got a genocide happening on our watch.

00:33:14.308 --> 00:33:24.843
We'll be mobilized to join the army and working with us to stop.

00:33:24.843 --> 00:33:30.367
How are the laws in the UK according to the life?

00:33:30.367 --> 00:33:36.085
Our laws in the UK are complicated in that.

00:33:36.085 --> 00:33:40.419
Abortion is actually illegal. People don't realize abortion is illegal in the UK

00:33:40.419 --> 00:33:44.230
under the 1864 offenses against the person act.

00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:50.687
However, what they did in 1967 was they brought in the abortion act,

00:33:50.687 --> 00:33:54.324
which gave exceptions where women could have an abortion.

00:33:54.324 --> 00:33:58.678
So every abortion that takes place in the UK is an exceptional case.

00:33:58.678 --> 00:34:06.080
We have 200,000 plus exceptional cases every single year.

00:34:07.279 --> 00:34:11.707
Most women don't realize, they think we have abortion on demand

00:34:11.707 --> 00:34:15.955
but by the letter of the law we we really don't and that's why we've got

00:34:15.955 --> 00:34:25.578
pro-abortion politicians and lobbyists trying to scrap that original 1864 part of the act

00:34:25.578 --> 00:34:27.953
that protects the unborn child.

00:34:27.953 --> 00:34:35.301
As we speak, back in the UK they are trying to, they call it decriminalize abortion,

00:34:35.301 --> 00:34:40.013
so that babies will no longer have any protection in the womb.

00:34:40.013 --> 00:34:47.435
Currently it's up to 24 weeks and if two doctors sign for it to say that,

00:34:47.435 --> 00:34:52.003
normally most of them are under mental health, so they'll say that if the woman continues

00:34:52.003 --> 00:34:55.563
with this pregnancy it will impact her mental health.

00:34:55.563 --> 00:34:58.010
The forms are pre signed.

00:34:58.010 --> 00:35:04.200
Then after 24 weeks a woman can abort her baby all the way up to birth

00:35:04.200 --> 00:35:08.321
for any perceived abnormality, whether Down syndrome,

00:35:08.321 --> 00:35:16.161
whether even cleft lip pet or if there's deemed a risk to the woman's life.

00:35:16.161 --> 00:35:20.000
That's the situation we've got at the moment.

00:35:20.440 --> 00:35:27.585
And do you have some contact with a women who already had an abortion

00:35:27.585 --> 00:35:31.984
and they say where were you when I had my abortion

00:35:31.984 --> 00:35:36.849
or I wish I listen to you or something like that?

00:35:36.849 --> 00:35:38.975
Do you have that?

00:35:38.975 --> 00:35:46.463
Very early on there was this lady and she came and saw our images and she said,

00:35:46.463 --> 00:35:51.492
you could tell visually she was distressed, but she said I didn't know it had fingers,

00:35:51.492 --> 00:35:53.403
I didn't know it had toes.

00:35:53.403 --> 00:36:01.853
They told me it was just a clump of cellls. If I knew then this my baby might be here today.

00:36:01.853 --> 00:36:06.537
As much as every woman doesn't articulate it in that way,

00:36:06.537 --> 00:36:13.648
we know that does impact a lot of women and that's why it's so important in the pro-life movement

00:36:13.648 --> 00:36:17.165
that we have places that we can point these women to.

00:36:17.165 --> 00:36:20.423
We have a project called Pace post abortion support for everyone.

00:36:20.423 --> 00:36:26.926
The lady who runs that, she had an abortion back in the 60s and

00:36:26.926 --> 00:36:32.061
she helps people go through recovery course

00:36:32.061 --> 00:36:37.502
and that is very much bringing the love of God into their lives.

00:36:37.502 --> 00:36:41.886
Helping that to come to the place of acknowledgement of what it was that they done

00:36:41.886 --> 00:36:45.942
but also then repentance and healing as well.

00:36:45.942 --> 00:36:50.591
This is obviously a massive necessary part of the pro-life movement

00:36:50.591 --> 00:36:53.924
and these women often go on to share their testimonies

00:36:53.924 --> 00:36:58.880
and stories and can be a powerful force for change.

00:36:58.880 --> 00:37:05.035
Because as much as the abortion industry is saying that women need abortion,

00:37:05.035 --> 00:37:10.116
these women are saying I wish I never had that right, I wish the doctor never

00:37:10.116 --> 00:37:13.505
offered me the right to kill my child.

00:37:13.505 --> 00:37:20.388
Our heart, as no doubt yours does too, goes out to these women and men as well.

00:37:20.388 --> 00:37:24.469
Because men are impacted by abortion as well.

00:37:24.469 --> 00:37:29.262
So it's very important that we help, support these women.

00:37:29.262 --> 00:37:34.861
What do you tell people who often say to us

00:37:34.861 --> 00:37:38.429
„oh it's because you are religious or something like that“?

00:37:38.429 --> 00:37:44.129
How do you defend life without using religion language?

00:37:44.129 --> 00:37:48.248
For us, because we let the images do the talking,

00:37:48.248 --> 00:37:52.319
image isn't really a religious argument.

00:37:52.319 --> 00:37:54.649
It's just simply the truth.

00:37:54.649 --> 00:37:59.722
People sometimes still say it „oh you're just doing this because you're a Christian“

00:37:59.722 --> 00:38:03.367
and then we just point them to our atheist volunteer

00:38:03.367 --> 00:38:07.259
and then they'll say like well you're there, it's just a distraction.

00:38:07.259 --> 00:38:12.231
It doesn't matter who is making the arguments, they won't agree with.

00:38:12.231 --> 00:38:15.918
It's like if it's a man they'll say 'you're just a man' and then

00:38:15.918 --> 00:38:18.607
if you say would you like to talk to a female - no.

00:38:18.607 --> 00:38:28.801
So it's just a distraction but scientifically human life begins at that point of fertilization

00:38:28.801 --> 00:38:33.284
and a sperm is not a human being, an egg is not a human being.

00:38:33.284 --> 00:38:36.115
But when they come together at the moment of fertilization

00:38:36.115 --> 00:38:40.645
you have a whole unique living human being that's got everything it needs to grow,

00:38:40.645 --> 00:38:46.803
unless an abortion comes in and intentionally ends that life.

00:38:46.803 --> 00:38:50.262
That's a scientific argument.

00:38:50.262 --> 00:38:57.593
So you don't need to be a Christian or have a religious faith to know that killing is wrong.

00:38:57.593 --> 00:39:04.755
Most people who don't have a faith would agree with the laws that

00:39:04.755 --> 00:39:07.020
prevent murdering born people.

00:39:07.020 --> 00:39:11.173
So we're just trying to extend that same right to unborn people.

00:39:11.173 --> 00:39:17.614
The problem is obviously that they don't see the unborn person as fully human.

00:39:17.614 --> 00:39:22.358
That's why it's our job as pro-lifers to make that argument,

00:39:22.358 --> 00:39:29.679
particularly using images and whatever other means we have such as scientific arguments.

00:39:29.679 --> 00:39:32.422
Such as the heart starts beating at 21 days.

00:39:32.422 --> 00:39:34.964
So many people are not aware of that.

00:39:34.964 --> 00:39:38.405
They think that the heart's beating months in cuz some people,

00:39:38.405 --> 00:39:43.979
when you ask them, is it wrong to stop a beating heart, they'll say 'well yes'.

00:39:43.979 --> 00:39:48.005
And then when you say did you know that their heart starts beating at 21 days?

00:39:48.005 --> 00:39:50.112
They didn't have any idea.

00:39:50.112 --> 00:39:55.882
That would get rid of most abortions right so the science is fundamental

00:39:55.882 --> 00:40:03.110
and I would say where the science fails is it can't tell us who's valuable

00:40:03.110 --> 00:40:06.017
and where does value come from.

00:40:06.017 --> 00:40:08.341
That's where now that becomes a religious question.

00:40:08.341 --> 00:40:16.136
Because if we leave human rights and value of people down to human beings,

00:40:16.136 --> 00:40:21.571
that's why throughout history we've seen different groups of people

00:40:21.571 --> 00:40:25.844
whether it was the Jews during the time of the Holocaust, whether it was the Africans

00:40:25.844 --> 00:40:28.180
at the time of the transatlantic slave trade.

00:40:28.180 --> 00:40:33.604
We've seen people groups dehumanized because human beings have tried

00:40:33.604 --> 00:40:39.462
to say you're not quite as human or as valuable as us.

00:40:39.462 --> 00:40:43.227
That's exactly what we're seeing with the unborn child.

00:40:43.227 --> 00:40:50.300
That's why people of faith, particularly Christians, are able to say:

00:40:50.300 --> 00:40:55.772
„No. As long as you're human you are made and created in the image of God

00:40:55.772 --> 00:40:58.298
and you have inherent value.

00:40:58.298 --> 00:41:03.167
It doesn't matter what ethnicity you are, it doesn't matter whether

00:41:03.167 --> 00:41:08.257
you're male or female, even the way you choose to live your life“.

00:41:08.257 --> 00:41:13.103
That doesn't take away from your inherent value and your inherent right to life

00:41:13.103 --> 00:41:17.966
because you're made in the image of your Creator and it doesn't matter what kind

00:41:17.966 --> 00:41:20.125
of circumstances surrounding your conception.

00:41:20.125 --> 00:41:23.450
Whether you're conceived in rape, whether you were conceived in a loving relationship.

00:41:23.450 --> 00:41:27.201
You have inherent value simply because you are here,

00:41:27.201 --> 00:41:30.897
you were born, you were living in the womb.

00:41:30.897 --> 00:41:33.802
So that's where our value comes from.

00:41:33.802 --> 00:41:39.124
And that's a very important topic that we need for any injustice.

00:41:39.124 --> 00:41:43.893
How do you recruit your people, your volunteers?

00:41:43.893 --> 00:41:50.000
Do you go somewhere and call them to come, or they see you at the street

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:54.261
and they say 'okay, how can I be as you are', or…?

00:41:54.261 --> 00:41:59.123
I would say most people are recruited from either presentations,

00:41:59.123 --> 00:42:02.638
we go and do presentations to explain about our work.

00:42:02.638 --> 00:42:07.833
Often in churches, sometimes in educational places.

00:42:07.833 --> 00:42:11.751
And as well as our social media online.

00:42:11.751 --> 00:42:15.700
We put lots of videos, we have lots of footage on the street where we interview people.

00:42:15.700 --> 00:42:17.076
We put those videos out there.

00:42:17.076 --> 00:42:21.518
People come across our work and we encourage them to join the movement,

00:42:21.518 --> 00:42:24.093
to get involved where they are.

00:42:24.093 --> 00:42:26.302
So those two ways are the ways we reach people.

00:42:26.302 --> 00:42:33.372
I would like to ask you personally, where is the source of your strength?

00:42:33.372 --> 00:42:36.772
How do you do this all these years?

00:42:36.772 --> 00:42:41.176
It is God, it is my faith in God.

00:42:41.176 --> 00:42:44.668
Ultimately I work for Him.

00:42:44.668 --> 00:42:46.532
I whilst I work for CBR UK,

00:42:46.532 --> 00:42:51.580
I'm working for God because I believe that this grieves the heart of God

00:42:51.580 --> 00:42:54.452
on the deep level.

00:42:54.452 --> 00:43:01.738
We've never seen such a genocide on just simply on the scale that we're seeing.

00:43:01.738 --> 00:43:10.759
75 million lives intentionally killed by abortion every year across the world.

00:43:10.759 --> 00:43:15.702
It's mass genocide and it grieves the heart of God because these babies,

00:43:15.702 --> 00:43:19.819
these human beings who's created for a purpose on earth

00:43:19.819 --> 00:43:22.029
don't even get to see the light of day.

00:43:22.029 --> 00:43:29.763
So I just gain strength through Him,

00:43:29.763 --> 00:43:35.359
through His word, through the friendship of those

00:43:35.359 --> 00:43:39.438
on the team working together on this mission.

00:43:39.438 --> 00:43:43.128
It's strengthening, encouraging one another when you face opposition from outside,

00:43:43.128 --> 00:43:48.830
it is strengthening and this is what helps.

00:43:48.830 --> 00:43:54.810
What can you say about the people who get in your organization

00:43:54.810 --> 00:43:58.690
and they're non-believers, and they are believers?

00:43:58.690 --> 00:44:04.720
What is the main thing why they come? Is it the truth?

00:44:04.720 --> 00:44:12.376
We do have some volunteers who are part of our teams on the street, who are not Christian.

00:44:12.376 --> 00:44:15.218
You don't have to be a Christian to come and volunteer on our teams.

00:44:15.218 --> 00:44:20.897
One particular lady who comes to mind, very faithful, amazing volunteer,

00:44:20.897 --> 00:44:25.275
she's a vegan, atheist and she's animal rights.

00:44:25.275 --> 00:44:33.249
She's very activist in the animal rights area and she thought to herself

00:44:33.249 --> 00:44:39.411
'how can I be kind of campaigning for another species while my own species

00:44:39.411 --> 00:44:42.619
is being killed in the womb?'

00:44:42.619 --> 00:44:47.493
So she got involved because of that and she actually gets a lot of hate

00:44:47.493 --> 00:44:51.468
from the animal rights people for her involvement in pro-life.

00:44:51.468 --> 00:44:57.616
I think she sees the contrast because we are very supportive of her

00:44:57.616 --> 00:45:00.092
and the different work that she does.

00:45:00.092 --> 00:45:06.221
It's truth, she's seen the truth, she's got a soft heart and she believes the truth

00:45:06.221 --> 00:45:09.939
and she wants to fight on behalf of these babies and be their voice.

00:45:09.939 --> 00:45:15.455
As I said you don't have to be a person of faith or Christian

00:45:15.455 --> 00:45:20.266
or another religious faith to want to stand up.

00:45:20.266 --> 00:45:23.997
And you said that you have 12 teams in the UK?

00:45:23.997 --> 00:45:25.647
Yes.

00:45:25.647 --> 00:45:27.604
How do you organize yourself?

00:45:27.604 --> 00:45:33.517
Do you say 'today we are coming and we are going to be there for this

00:45:33.517 --> 00:45:37.522
and this much of hours' and who can come,

00:45:37.522 --> 00:45:40.991
let them come or how do you organize?

00:45:40.991 --> 00:45:45.020
Well each team has a team leader, then regional team leader

00:45:45.020 --> 00:45:47.613
and they organize when they're going to go out.

00:45:47.613 --> 00:45:51.686
They tend to typically go out once a month to their city center.

00:45:51.686 --> 00:45:56.521
We have someone who oversees the team, who's doing an amazing job.

00:45:56.521 --> 00:46:03.115
She's just encouraging them all, gathering them on zoom or online

00:46:03.115 --> 00:46:07.233
to encourage one another, to train each other.

00:46:07.233 --> 00:46:11.621
We have annual kind of gathering,

00:46:11.621 --> 00:46:16.125
where we all come together and again just encourage one another.

00:46:16.125 --> 00:46:22.280
How long do you stay in a particular day, how long are you outside?

00:46:22.280 --> 00:46:25.110
For a couple, a few hours, about two hours.

00:46:25.110 --> 00:46:27.090
And how many people?

00:46:27.090 --> 00:46:33.307
Typically our target is around 10 people, so we have about three people holding the banners,

00:46:33.307 --> 00:46:36.162
then we have people handing out leaflets.

00:46:36.162 --> 00:46:41.378
We have the team leader, we've actually developed the role of a photo journalist.

00:46:41.378 --> 00:46:44.454
So a lot of our teams have photojournalists

00:46:44.454 --> 00:46:46.919
and as I say they're just there to film what's happening,

00:46:46.919 --> 00:46:49.157
to send it back to us on social media.

00:46:49.157 --> 00:46:54.638
So that we can show what's happening, show how public opinion is at the moment.

00:46:54.638 --> 00:46:57.758
And we're very sincere about that.

00:46:57.758 --> 00:47:01.558
We show those who are pro-choice, we show those who are pro-life

00:47:01.558 --> 00:47:07.462
and we're just putting that out there for people to see.

00:47:07.462 --> 00:47:11.141
It's our hope that we'll continue to see more and more changed minds

00:47:11.141 --> 00:47:14.310
and to see and document that shift in public opinion.

00:47:14.310 --> 00:47:19.830
So everyone's got a role. We also have, I think I forgot to mention earlier,

00:47:19.830 --> 00:47:26.550
I did say we film our displays just to make sure if one makes any false accusation

00:47:26.550 --> 00:47:31.502
against us and it helps deter who would be attackers as well.

00:47:31.502 --> 00:47:34.502
And how do you collect the money for your work?

00:47:34.502 --> 00:47:39.360
Is it out of donations or some kind of fundraising or…?

00:47:39.360 --> 00:47:43.909
Yes, we have individuals from around the country who have seen what we're doing

00:47:43.909 --> 00:47:45.293
and encouraged what we're doing.

00:47:45.293 --> 00:47:50.936
They maybe want to see an end to an abortion and they believe in our vision and in our mission.

00:47:50.936 --> 00:47:54.605
And they support us financially.

00:47:54.605 --> 00:47:57.620
Some churches as well will give us support.

00:47:58.134 --> 00:48:06.950
Can you tell someone who's out there, why shouldn't they get an abortion

00:48:06.950 --> 00:48:11.910
or why should they get involved in a prolife movement?

00:48:11.910 --> 00:48:14.709
Just maybe for the end.

00:48:14.709 --> 00:48:22.022
I would say if you're pregnant and maybe you don't want to be,

00:48:22.022 --> 00:48:25.104
maybe you're in a challenging situation,

00:48:25.104 --> 00:48:32.647
just have hope and just know that that is already a living human being, living inside you.

00:48:32.647 --> 00:48:34.010
Not just any human being.

00:48:34.010 --> 00:48:39.506
That's your own child made in your image but also made in the image of God.

00:48:39.506 --> 00:48:47.189
And He has placed that baby inside of you and you are enough to look after that baby.

00:48:47.189 --> 00:48:49.374
Even if you can't, there's adoption out there.

00:48:49.374 --> 00:48:53.527
But you know your child doesn't deserve the death sentences because

00:48:53.527 --> 00:48:58.975
of maybe mistakes that we have made here on earth.

00:48:58.975 --> 00:49:02.052
So I would just say there's support out there.

00:49:02.052 --> 00:49:05.281
Find, go online, whether it's in Croatia,

00:49:05.281 --> 00:49:09.613
I'm sure you can put at the bottom where they can go for help.

00:49:09.613 --> 00:49:14.082
In the UK just Google 'support during pregnancy',

00:49:14.082 --> 00:49:17.835
I'm sure you'll get some support out there.

00:49:17.835 --> 00:49:21.046
Just have your baby and love your baby.

00:49:21.046 --> 00:49:26.633
Thank you. And how can you encourage people maybe here in Croatia

00:49:26.633 --> 00:49:33.100
to involve in 40 Days for Life, in Croatia for Life, or pro-life movement in our country?

00:49:33.100 --> 00:49:36.954
What is the special thing about being in pro-life?

00:49:36.954 --> 00:49:45.699
I think it's just caring about life, caring about justice.

00:49:45.699 --> 00:49:50.000
Whilst you may feel that this issue hasn't touched you personally,

00:49:50.000 --> 00:49:55.000
when there's injustice anywhere, it affects justice everywhere.

00:49:55.000 --> 00:49:59.684
I would just say get involved.

00:49:59.684 --> 00:50:05.039
I'm sure they can contact you and just be part of this growing pro-life movement

00:50:05.039 --> 00:50:07.132
because it is growing.

00:50:07.132 --> 00:50:11.205
And be on the right side of history because one day we're going to look back

00:50:11.205 --> 00:50:14.659
and you know our children and our children's children going to ask us

00:50:14.659 --> 00:50:19.473
what did you do when the biggest genocide was happening?

00:50:19.473 --> 00:50:22.541
Did you look away and just get on with your comfortable life

00:50:22.541 --> 00:50:28.571
or did you step in the fight and defend these babies and their mothers?

00:50:28.571 --> 00:50:31.341
Thank you Ruth so much.

00:50:31.341 --> 00:50:35.937
I'm really thrilled to have you here and to talk to you

00:50:35.937 --> 00:50:42.403
and I wish you a good time here in our country and hope to see you soon.

00:50:42.403 --> 00:50:48.156
Oh thank you so much Lydia, it's been wonderful to be here, to see you again and to be in Croatia.

00:50:48.156 --> 00:50:50.951
God bless the work you're doing, it's amazing.

00:50:50.951 --> 00:50:56.816
Thank you. Dear followers of the "Croatia for Life" channel,

00:50:56.816 --> 00:50:59.289
this is the end of another of our podcast.

00:50:59.289 --> 00:51:04.012
We had our dear guest from the United Kingdom, Ruth Rawlins.

00:51:04.012 --> 00:51:07.667
Keep following us! Praised Jesus and Mary!

